group_1.textLeft: Welcome, Rabi. We got some@great vegetables here!

group_1.textRight: ...Oh, I had heard that the cabbages@didn't do well,
but these have bright and healthy leaves,@and the price itself is reasonable.

group_1.textLeft: I did my best to get this stock in.
Still, I was hoping to sell them@for more...
It's been raining so much that@it's hard to get customers...

group_1.textRight: That sounds rough.@I'll buy two from you, then.

group_1.textLeft: You mean it?! Two's pretty big @though, you know?

group_1.textRight: It's just a matter of coming up with different@dishes to eat them before they spoil.

group_1.textLeft: I gotcha, thanks. I'll throw in some@potatoes as a bonus.

group_1.textRight: Then how about some of our mackerel?@Maybe some stir-fry with your cabbages?

group_1.textLeft: Fishmonger! Quit trying to piggyback@off my sale!

group_1.textRight: Mackerel...is good, but I think@I'll get some cod.
I'll make white fish poêlé with potatoes,@cabbage, and cod.

group_1.textLeft: Never heard of a dish like that before.
You really are the second Yachiyo Nanami.@Thank you for your continued support!
You don't know?@Isn't that what everyone calls you?
You're young, you're an excellent shopper,@and you neeeever miss your ten times the points.

group_1.textRight: What...? I suppose I stand out a little.

group_1.textLeft: Lady Nayuta, are you heading home now?

group_1.textRight: I was wondering if you would be@in the shopping district,
so I took a detour, and bingo.
I will help you with the shopping.

group_1.textLeft: If that is what you're up to,@then I am glad to hear it.
Taking one of these eco bags@would be helpful.

group_1.textRight: *Giggle* I'll carry it safely to the end!

group_1.textLeft: You're in quite a good mood.

group_1.textRight: *Giggle* That is because I received my test@back today and got a perfect score.
And in math of all things!@It's put me in a wonderful mood!

group_1.textLeft: You had told me you weren't@that great at it.
That will only turn the tables back on you,@so I would recommend you refrain from that.
I would prefer to not see my master utterly@devastated by an elementary schooler.
